    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <head>No. 494.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">de
                                    Zamacona</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-02-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 19,
                                    1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I had the honor to receive upon the 15th
                            instant the note of Mr. Navarro, the chargé d’affaires <hi rend="italic">ad interim</hi> of Mexico, bearing date the 10th of the present
                            month, in which, by direction of his government, he has informed me that
                            it is the desire of Mexico that the treaty between it and the United
                            States of July 10, 1868, concerning naturalization and citizenship,
                            shall be terminated at the expiration of the twelve months, as provided
                            for in article 5 of such convention.</p>
                <p>Observing that due note has been taken of this announcement, I take the
                            present occasion to offer, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
